Hello Ng Zi Kai,

You can determine the number of hops from seed by looking at the path-from-seed, which is the 5th column in crawl.log. The number of letters in that field is the number of hops from seed (unless it&#39;s more than 50 hops in which case it will be abbreviated).

It is possible to write separate crawl logs for the different numbers of hops, but it&#39;s not simple to configure. My suggestion would be to split the crawl log up in a postprocessing step, by examining the path-from-seed for each crawled url.

Noah


